<header>
<h2><a href="http://www.dogshaming.com/2013/10/thunderstruck/" rel="bookmark" title="Thunderstruck!">Thunderstruck!</a></h2>
</header> <!-- end article header -->


<figure class="vignette overlay inset">
<a href="http://www.dogshaming.com/2013/10/thunderstruck/" title="Thunderstruck!"><img src="http://i2.wp.com/www.dogshaming.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/thunderstorm.jpg?fit=637%2C1000" class="attachment-large wp-post-image" alt="thunderstorm" /></a>
</figure>


<section class="post_content clearfix">

<p><a href="http://i2.wp.com/www.dogshaming.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/thunderstorm.jpg"></a></p>
<p>Bailey is a 4 year old border collie mix. We got him from a family that originally adopted him to be a guard dog. As you can see, he is a pretty big wimp. We have some pretty epic summer thunderstorms and I&#8217;ve never seen him this terrified before!</p>
</section> <!-- end article section -->

<a href="http://www.dogshaming.com/2013/10/suitcase-of-shame/" title="SUITCASE OF SHAME!"><img src="http://i1.wp.com/www.dogshaming.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image337.jpg?fit=637%2C1000" class="attachment-large wp-post-image" alt="image337" /></a>
